This paper uses machine learning to analyze the citation dynamics of scientific publications funded by government funding agencies, which falls under the domain of digital libraries (cs.DL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The study also involves statistical analysis and modeling, which aligns with the categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the implications of funding policies and their impact on scientific research, which could be relevant to the category of computers and society (cs.CY).
